			    STPJS 298</div>
  <p class="cont">may destroy<span class="footRef">1</span>&mdash;any person that he can find that will yield to him, he will bind him,<span class="footRef">2</span> and take
  possession of the body<span class="footRef">3</span> and reign there, glorying in it mightily, not caring that he had got merely
  a stolen body; and by and by some one having authority will come along and cast him out<span class="footRef">4</span> and
  restore the tabernacle to its rightful owner.<span class="footRef">5</span> The devil steals a tabernacle because he has not one of
  his own: but if he steals one, he is always liable to be turned out of doors.</p>
  <div class="topic">Calling and Election</div>
  <p class="std">Now, there is some grand secret<span class="footRef">6</span> here, and keys to unlock the subject. Notwithstanding the
  apostle exhorts them to add to their faith, virtue, knowledge, temperance,<span class="footRef">7</span> etc., yet he exhorts them
  to make their calling and election sure.<span class="footRef">8</span> And though they had heard an audible voice from heaven
  bearing testimony that Jesus was the Son of God,<span class="footRef">9</span> yet he says we have a more sure word of
  prophecy, whereunto ye do well that ye take heed as unto a light shining in a dark place.<span class="footRef">10</span> Now,
  wherein could they have a more sure word of prophecy than to hear the voice of God saying, This
  is my beloved Son.<span class="footRef">11</span></p>
  <p class="std">Now for the secret and grand key. Though they might hear the voice of God and know that Jesus
  was the Son of God, this would be no evidence that their election and calling was made sure, that
  they had part with Christ,<span class="footRef">12</span> and were joint heirs with Him.<span class="footRef">13</span> They then would want that more sure
  word of prophecy,<span class="footRef">14</span> that they were sealed in the heavens<span class="footRef">15</span> and had the promise of eternal life in the
  kingdom of God.<span class="footRef">16</span> Then, having this promise sealed<span class="footRef">17</span> unto them, it was an anchor to the soul, sure
  and steadfast.<span class="footRef">18</span> Though the thunders might roll and lightnings flash, and earthquakes bellow, and
  war gather thick around, yet this hope and knowledge would support the soul in every hour of trial,
  trouble and tribulation.<span class="footRef">19</span> Then knowledge through our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ<span class="footRef">20</span> is the grand
  key that unlocks the glories and mysteries of the kingdom<span class="footRef">21</span> of heaven.</p>
  <p class="std">Compare this principle once with Christendom at the present day, and where are they, with all
  their boasted religion, piety and sacredness while at the same time they are crying out against
  prophets, apostles, angels, revelations, prophesying and visions, etc. Why, they are just ripening for
  the damnation<span class="footRef">22</span> of hell.<span class="footRef">23</span> They will be damned, for they reject the most glorious principles of the
  Gospel of Jesus Christ<span class="footRef">24</span> and treat with disdain</p>
